  <prompt>
    Refresh docs/architecture/INSIGHTS-ENGINE-ARCHITECTURE.md to reflect Phase 1.5 architectural decisions (D-P15-01..D-P15-09 from design.md). The §0a callout (Phase 1 + Phase 1.5 framing) was authored on 2026-05-30; this task updates the body with the post-design refinements (Terminology, no new sprk_prompt entity, practice areas sourced from sprk_practicearea_ref, etc.) and adds wave-organized status.
  </prompt>

  <role>Documentation architect + Spaarke-wide doc maintainer.</role>

  <goal>
    INSIGHTS-ENGINE-ARCHITECTURE.md body sections incorporate the Phase 1.5 refinements; the document accurately reflects (a) Terminology (JPS vs PlaybookExecutionEngine vs INodeExecutor vs sprk_analysisaction); (b) the 2D practice-area × document-type taxonomy; (c) multi-entity subject scheme; (d) hybrid playbook + RAG consumption; (e) prompts in sprk_analysisaction (no new entity). r2 design.md and spec.md remain the canonical Phase 1.5 references; the architecture doc points readers to them where appropriate.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="canonical-arch">docs/architecture/INSIGHTS-ENGINE-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    <file purpose="phase-1.5-design">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="phase-1.5-spec">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/spec.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="docs-architecture-skill">Use the docs-architecture skill conventions when refreshing</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md PR-1">Do NOT introduce a new sprk_prompt entity in any architectural diagrams or text</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Read existing arch doc + §0a callout">Identify sections that need refresh per Phase 1.5 decisions</step>
    <step order="2" name="Invoke docs-architecture skill">Or refresh inline; update Terminology section, 2D taxonomy section, multi-entity subject section, prompt-storage section</step>
    <step order="3" name="Update cross-refs">Ensure design.md, spec.md, plan.md links work</step>
    <step order="4" name="Verify drift">Re-check doc against spec.md for any remaining inconsistencies</step>
  </steps>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">docs/architecture/INSIGHTS-ENGINE-ARCHITECTURE.md (modified)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Terminology section accurately defines JPS, PlaybookExecutionEngine, INodeExecutor, sprk_analysisaction</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No reference to a "sprk_prompt" entity (it was superseded per PR-1)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Practice-area examples reference real codes from sprk_practicearea_ref (no hardcoded "litigation/real-estate/patent/transactional")</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Cross-refs to design.md, spec.md, plan.md, CLAUDE.md work</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
